===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la}} {{term|idea|lang=la||a (Platonic) idea; archetype}}, from {{etyl|grc|en}} {{term|ἰδέα||notion, pattern|tr=idea|lang=grc|sc=polytonic}}, from {{term|εἴδω||I see|tr=eidō|lang=grc|sc=polytonic}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ʌɪˈdɪə/}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/aɪˈdiə/}}, {{SAMPA|/aI"di@/}}
* {{a|US}} rarely {{IPA|/aɪˈdiɚ/}}
* {{audio|en-us-idea.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|ɪə}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|head|pl=ideæ|pl2=ideas}}

# {{philosophy}} An abstract [[archetype]] of a given thing, compared to which real-life examples are seen as imperfect [[approximation]]s; pure [[essence]], as opposed to actual examples. {{defdate|from 14th c.}}
# {{obsolete}} The conception of someone or something as representing a perfect [[example]]; an [[ideal]]. {{defdate|16th-19th c.}}
# {{obsolete}} The [[form]] or [[shape]] of something; a quintessential [[aspect]] or [[characteristic]]. {{defdate|16th-18th c.}}
#* '''1603''', John Florio, translating Michel de Montaigne, ''Essays'', II.6:
#*: The remembrance whereof (which yet I beare deepely imprinted in my minde) representing me her visage and '''''Idea''''' so lively and so naturally, doth in some sort reconcile me unto her.
# An [[image]] of an object that is formed in the mind or recalled by the memory. {{defdate|from 16th c.}}
#: ''The mere '''idea''' of you is enough to excite me.''
# More generally, any result of mental activity; a [[thought]], a [[notion]]; a way of thinking. {{defdate|from 17th c.}}
#: ''Ideas'' won't go to jail.—A. Whitney Griswold (1952)
# A conception in the mind of something to be done; a [[plan]] for doing something, an {{l|en|intention}}. {{defdate|from 17th c.}}
#: ''I have an '''idea''' of how we might escape.''
# A vague or fanciful {{l|en|notion}}; a [[feeling]] or [[hunch]]; an [[impression]]. {{defdate|from 17th c.}}
#: ''He had the wild '''idea''' that if he leant forward a little, he might be able to touch the mountain-top.''
# {{music}} A [[musical]] [[theme]] or [[melodic]] [[subject]]. {{defdate|from 18th c.}}

